New Titles (1995)       
_____________________________________________________________________________   
    
REGISTERS/ (PEOPLE IN ALL) by Clark Coolidge    
88 pages        ISBN 0-939691-10-8      $9.95   
    
Written between May '89 and August '92, these fifty sections of 3-line  
stanza/chords continue Coolidge's fast-forward drive to explore how     
sheets of sound can be made to echo thought itself:         
    ." . . . Off where      
nerves rattle and glance interminable, the sphere of the bygone     
syllable. Lit as if sound, a cascade to a bell."        
    
(OUTSIDE) by Todd Baron     
88 pages        ISBN 0-939691-11-6      $9.95   
    
"Todd Baron's poems in (OUTSIDE) have a clarity that is not being   
either speech or thought while seeming the reverberation of 'the    
public' from inside 'someone,' "not lines or rhythms or even/ anything  
from the outside but on paper from the voice above the water-level/     
shouting something beneath." The sense of the poems' shape crosses a    
spatial line or level they make that is public/interior." Leslie    
Scalapino   
    
