X-To:     nada@twics.com    
In-Reply-To:  <199502021540.HAA13272@slip-1.slip.net>       
    
Dear Nada,  
Hello, I'm very glad you jumped in.     
I hope my statements have not been taken as being in any way against    
anyone's wish or need to speak out on anything. This forum seems very   
open (maybe even "wide open"), which is one of the best things about it.    
I might remind you though, that what is pleasurable for the speaker may     
not be for part or all of the listeners.    
As for what the level of poetry is, I'm not going to try that one.      
Poetry/art has its own level, and whatever it is or may be, it is not the   
same as theory or criticism or writers' discourses or internet exchanges.   
This view may strike some as extreme, simplistic or old-fashioned, but I    
think it's dangerous when artists or critics start saying (or building  
contexts in which) their discourse is on the same level as the art.     
Spencer Selby   
