>     In Clemens Hall, deconstruction crews continued putting the   
> program's infrastructure back together -- piece by piece. Yesterday, a    
> disconnected modem line from Buffalo's outskirts into the nerve center of 
> the university started running. Officials expected it would take five or  
> six months to get the entire network humming. 
>     ``Our biggest concern now is that people will lose hope,'' said   
> Jena Osman, the local official responsible for one of the recent benefits.    
