I cant remember the details of the context in whixh Cienfuegos made     
his sharp comment on revolutionary art. I read an account in a      
Mexican newspaper (this a short time before C.'s plane disappeared),    
and I do remember that the contxt (for the newspaper story) was that    
Cienfuegos seemd to have Fidel's ear, and the hope was that the CP      
would not come along and impose its usual ban on Freud, surrealism,     
etc. I should have been a auto-clipping service at the time.    
