>     AMHERST (AHP) -- Cabinet Ministers for the Poetics Program    
> want the poetry ``mafia'' to give up more than 6 years of control     
> over the bustling, pungent stalls of the nation's largest ``fish      
> market.'' 
>     Minister of Foreign Policy Robert Creeley announced plans     
> for the "Wednesdays at Four Plus" commission to better regulate and   
> investigate poets and critics doing business with the Poetics Program.    
>     ``New York mayor Rudolf Giuliani's plan for Fulton Fish   
> Market gave me the idea,'' said Creeley, who declared an emergency    
> meeting of the Poetics Program to unveil the plan.  ``The association     
> was natural -- fish, Olson, poetry, Buffalo ... it's your classic mob     
> situation.''  
>   
> ---More---    
