> approximately 50 people a reading to only 5 or 10.        
>     ``Students do not attend because they fear the readings are   
> only payback for favors,'' said a smiling Raymond Federman, newly     
> appointed Ambassador to France, a cabinet level position in the   
> current administration.       
>     Some poets say New York's Segue family uses its control over  
> students at the university to impose a monopolistic ``tax'' on    
> discussion driving many to do business at other markets on the    
> Eastern Seaboard.         
>     The allegations have never been substantiated.        
