Subject:  Espousing 2/9     
    
Thanks to everyone who voiced an opinion on whether these updates should    
continue landing on the poetics-list.  The current vote (including some     
back-channel communications) stands at 15-2 for continuing here.  We've     
also gotten some good advice about how else to use the Net (especially from 
Sandra Braman).  More as that develops.     
    
What follows is an especially long update (if you read nothing else, do at  
least check out "National Security Concerns," where a Jack Collum poem is   
credited with directly undermining the nation's armed services).    
    
We'll probably be off-line now until early next week as we travel to NYC    
for Jennifer's reading with Bill Luoma on Saturday at the Ear and Rae   
Armantrout/Lisa Jarnot/Lee Ann Brown's reading at Segue on Sunday.  So:     
Good luck to Bob, Susan, and Gil in Philadelphia on Saturday!       
    
Steve Evans & Jennifer Moxley       
1-401-274-1306  
    
