> that listed the Brown experiment as one of 154 studies involving      
> translation and human subjects. However, the Bureau now acknowledges  
> the substance used at Brown, waldrop-50, is not translative, said     
> Michael Palmer, deputy director of the Bureau's Office of Human   
> Translation Experiments.      
