Subject:  p>q re parmenides, etc.   
    
p>q (if P, then Q) is TRUE WHENEVER p is FALSE --regardless of the truthvalue of
q (.e.g.  if a and not a, then (whatever), is ALWAYS true, whether whatever is  
true or false.  
    
So i can start from something that is false and say anything i want.    
    
check it out    
    
    
    
"i cannot speak OF x" is FALSE because i am speaking of x.      
    
