  BUFFALO (AHP) - The struggling Buffalo Poetics        
 Program sent high profile scorer Susan Howe to the         
 Naropa Institute yesterday for veteran wingers Bobbie Louise       
 Hawkins and Anselm Hollo plus minor league defensewoman and recent     
 NEA recipient Eleni Sikelianos.    
  The Program, which has only one win in its last       
 five semesters, also sent a third-round pick in the 1999       
 admissions draft to the Institute as part of the deal.     
  Howe, who logged over a million miles last season to      
 lead the Program in travel time, had just two insights and three   
 inspired outbursts for five points in Buffalo's first 4 weeks      
 this year. 
  Hawkins and Hollo both played a significant role in       
 Naropa's last Holy Grail season, in 1993. In brief stints with the parent  
    
 ---More--- 
    
